      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CINNABAR ICON (3) has found the minor placings here at last couple of runs, finishing third last time beaten 5 lengths (22.66). Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings six times from 10 starts. Must come into calculations. UNCLE ERNEST (2) jumped from the pinch last start to lead all the way and score (22.55) at this track in Grade 5 over 390m. Has a strong record from box 2, including three wins. One of the key runners again. KRAKEN BABE (1) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 1.3 lengths at Bendigo in a handy 24.36. Draws the cherry and likes the trip. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Must be included in calculations. LIVING THE DREAM (4) dominated last start. Sure to run well again.",
